  "text": "A modification of the method of Ciukanu and Kerek [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] was employed for per-N,O-methylation of GSLs. GSLs (1-20 µg) were introduced into a conical-glass vial, and dimethyl sulfoxide (150 µL) was added without using special drying conditions or inert gas atmosphere. Powdered sodium hydroxide (40-60 mg), ground with an agate mortar and pestle, dried at 100",
